Dear Hiring Team,

I am writing to apply for the *Software Engineer III (Full Stack)* role with *6sense*. I bring more than five years of professional experience building production software across *Java*, *Spring Boot*, *React*, *TypeScript*, *FastAPI*, *PostgreSQL*, *Redis*, *AWS*, and *CI/CD*, along with a Master of Science in Computer Science from Pace University.

At Sperse, I built a *customer-facing* multi-agent CRM platform in *Python*, *FastAPI*, *LangGraph*, and *LangChain* that delivered *scalable full-stack applications* for 10,000+ users, routing requests across 40+ specialized sub-agents with tenant-aware access control and *application security best practices*. I also shipped a *React* and *TypeScript* workflow builder with *HTML* and *CSS* components, created a custom Bitbucket *MCP* server for an *OpenAI Codex* review pipeline, and wired GitHub Actions *CI/CD* with automated testing so our *AI-powered developer tools* and autonomous agents could improve delivery quality without sacrificing reliability. At Qualitest, I designed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service in *Java* and *Spring Boot* with *PostgreSQL* and *Redis*, exposing *RESTful APIs* across cloud platforms such as *AWS* S3, Google Cloud Storage, and MinIO while driving technical design discussions and architecture decisions; I then tuned *PostgreSQL* for large datasets and orchestrated asynchronous processing with AWS Step Functions to improve high availability and root-cause analysis.

My academic and project work has strengthened the same engineering discipline this role demands. I built a distributed coding-agent orchestrator that applies *data structures*, *algorithms*, and *system design* to break work into dependency-aware task DAGs, and that experience reinforced how important clean, maintainable, well-tested code and clear communication are when building reliable systems. *6sense*'s mission to make every signal, every AI agent, and every revenue team more effective aligns with the way I like to work: owning the outcome, shipping durable fixes, and collaborating closely with engineers, product partners, and designers. I also value *Win as One Team* and *Stay Curious*, and I would welcome the chance to contribute that mindset to *6sense*.

Thank you for your time and consideration. I would be glad to discuss how my experience building full-stack systems, automation workflows, and production-grade backend services can help *6sense* deliver better software for its customers.

